{"key":"post-13473594","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>13473594</id>\n<content>It's a close toss up, but layering is definitely better.&amp;nbsp; I see no evidence whatever to back up claims above that mixing results in faster colonization.&amp;nbsp; Layering actually allows the mycelium to knit back together faster, and then it rips right into the bulk substrate.&amp;nbsp; Total time from spawning to fruiting is a bit faster if layering is used.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The above is for tray culture.&amp;nbsp; When using sterilized substrate in filter patch bags, I always shake the bags well after pouring the grain spawn in.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>13473804</next>\n<prev>13473295</prev>\n<first>13467477</first>\n<last>13478177</last>\n<when>1289590780</when>\n<utime>11/12/10 09:39 PM</utime>\n</post>"}